---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

export const prerender = true;

<Layout
  title="Terms of Service"
  description="Rhumb's terms of service. Scores are opinions, API is provided as-is, data licensed CC BY 4.0."
  canonical="/terms"
>
  <div class="bg-navy min-h-screen">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 pt-14 pb-24">
      <header class="mb-12">
        <span class="text-xs font-mono font-semibold text-amber uppercase tracking-widest">
          Legal
        </span>
        <h1 class="font-display font-bold text-3xl text-slate-100 leading-tight tracking-tight mt-4 mb-4">
          Terms of Service
        </h1>
        <p class="text-sm text-slate-500 font-mono">
          Last updated: March 11, 2026
        </p>
      </header>

      <div class="space-y-10 text-slate-400 text-sm leading-relaxed">
        <section>
          <h2 class="font-display font-bold text-xl text-slate-100 mb-3">
            1. Acceptance
          </h2>
          <p>
            By accessing Rhumb (&#8220;the Service&#8221;), operated by
            Supertrained LLC, you agree to these Terms of Service. If you
            disagree, please do not use the Service.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="font-display font-bold text-xl text-slate-100 mb-3">
            2. Nature of scores
          </h2>
          <p>
            AN Scores are{" "}
            <strong class="text-slate-200">
              opinions based on documentation analysis
            </strong>
            . They are not warranties, guarantees, or certifications of
            any kind. Scores reflect our assessment of how well a
            service&#39;s published documentation suggests it will work
            for autonomous AI agents.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-3">
            Scores may change as documentation is updated, methodologies
            are refined, or disputes are resolved. We make reasonable
            efforts to be accurate but do not guarantee the correctness
            of any individual score.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="font-display font-bold text-xl text-slate-100 mb-3">
            3. API usage
          </h2>
          <p>
            The Rhumb API is currently provided{" "}
            <strong class="text-slate-200">
              free of charge with no authentication required
            </strong>
            . This may change in the future — we will provide reasonable
            notice before requiring authentication or introducing usage
            limits.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-3">The API is provided as-is, with:</p>
          <ul class="space-y-2 mt-3">
            <li>
              &bull; No guaranteed uptime or service level agreement (SLA)
            </li>
            <li>
              &bull; No guaranteed response time or rate limit protections
            </li>
            <li>
              &bull; No commitment to backward compatibility of response
              schemas (we aim for stability but are at v0.3)
            </li>
          </ul>
          <p class="mt-3">
            We reserve the right to block or rate-limit abusive usage,
            including but not limited to: automated scraping at scale,
            denial-of-service attempts, or usage that degrades the
            service for other users.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="font-display font-bold text-xl text-slate-100 mb-3">
            4. Data licensing
          </h2>
          <ul class="space-y-3 mt-3">
            <li>
              <strong class="text-slate-200">
                Score data (AN Scores, failure modes, leaderboards):
              </strong>{" "}
              Licensed under{" "}
              <a
                href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener noreferrer"
                class="text-amber hover:underline underline-offset-2"
              >
                Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International (CC BY
                4.0)
              </a>
              . You may use, share, and adapt the data for any purpose,
              including commercial use, provided you give attribution.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong class="text-slate-200">Source code:</strong>{" "}
              Licensed under the{" "}
              <a
                href="https://opensource.org/licenses/MIT"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener noreferrer"
                class="text-amber hover:underline underline-offset-2"
              >
                MIT License
              </a>
              .
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong class="text-slate-200">
                Service guides and blog content:
              </strong>{" "}
              &copy; 2026 Supertrained LLC. All rights reserved unless
              otherwise noted.
            </li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="font-display font-bold text-xl text-slate-100 mb-3">
            5. Dispute process
          </h2>
          <p>
            If you believe a score is inaccurate, you may file a dispute
            via:
          </p>
          <ul class="space-y-2 mt-3">
            <li>
              &bull;{" "}
              <a
                href="https://github.com/supertrained/rhumb/issues/new"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener noreferrer"
                class="text-amber hover:underline underline-offset-2"
              >
                GitHub issue
              </a>{" "}
              (public)
            </li>
            <li>
              &bull;{" "}
              <a
                href="mailto:providers@supertrained.ai"
                class="text-amber hover:underline underline-offset-2"
              >
                providers@supertrained.ai
              </a>{" "}
              (private)
            </li>
          </ul>
          <p class="mt-3">
            We commit to reviewing every dispute and responding within 5
            business days. Outcomes of public disputes are published on
            GitHub. We reserve final editorial discretion on all scores.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="font-display font-bold text-xl text-slate-100 mb-3">
            6. Limitation of liability
          </h2>
          <p>
            The Service is provided &#8220;as is&#8221; without warranty
            of any kind, express or implied. Supertrained LLC shall not
            be liable for any damages arising from the use of AN Scores,
            failure mode data, or any other information provided through
            the Service.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-3">
            This includes but is not limited to: decisions made based on
            AN Scores, tool selection influenced by leaderboard rankings,
            or business impact from published failure mode data.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="font-display font-bold text-xl text-slate-100 mb-3">
            7. Changes to terms
          </h2>
          <p>
            We may update these terms. Material changes will be announced
            in our{" "}
            <a
              href="/changelog"
              class="text-amber hover:underline underline-offset-2"
            >
              changelog
            </a>{" "}
            and noted by updating the &#8220;Last updated&#8221; date.
            Continued use of the Service after changes constitutes
            acceptance.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="font-display font-bold text-xl text-slate-100 mb-3">
            8. Governing law
          </h2>
          <p>
            These Terms are governed by and construed in accordance with
            the laws of the State of California, United States.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="font-display font-bold text-xl text-slate-100 mb-3">
            9. Contact
          </h2>
          <p>
            For questions about these terms:
            <br />
            <a
              href="mailto:legal@supertrained.ai"
              class="text-amber hover:underline underline-offset-2"
            >
              legal@supertrained.ai
            </a>
          </p>
          <p class="mt-3">
            Supertrained LLC
            <br />
            Los Angeles, CA
          </p>
        </section>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
